#X text 594 280 THIS VERSION COMPARED TO PREVIOUS ONE WORKS BY OUTPUTTING RATIO OF CURRENT-TIME/BAR-DURATION AND SAVE INCOMING MIDI WITH THIS. PLAYBACK IS SIMPLY DONE BY COMPARING THE RATIO AGAIN WITH PRE-RECORDED RATIOS. SO THIS WAY BAR DURATION CHANGE WILL INCREASE/DECREASE PLAYBACK SPEED \; THIS ISSUE IS THAT IT IS NOT VERY ACCURATE ATLEAST WITH CURRENT "TEXT SEARCH" IMPLEMENTATION (UPTO AROUND 10ms OF ERROR) \; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- \; KEEP WORKING ON THIS METHOD AND MAYBE: \; 1 - USING REALTIME/TIMER OBJECTS INSTEAD OF ABSOLUTE-BAR-TIME IMPLEMENTATION (?). ISSUE WILL BE THAT THESE OBJECT CANNOT BE TURNEDOFF (MAYBE SOMEHOW YES?) AND CPU USAGE COULD BE AN ISSUE(?) \; 2 - AN EXTERNAL IMPLEMENTATION THAT ESPECIALLY SUBSTITUTE AND IMPROVES THE "TEXT SEARCH" OBJECT USAGE \;, f 73;
